                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17752914" author="sarkaramrit2@gmail.com" created="Thu, 10 Aug 2023 19:55:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CC &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=houston&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;houston&quot;&gt;houston&lt;/a&gt;, team: let me know if need more information.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17753285" author="houston" created="Fri, 11 Aug 2023 17:07:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;By defaulting the embedded ZK &lt;tt&gt;clientPortAddress&lt;/tt&gt;, the zk server cannot accept connections routed to a docker container. If we allow this setting to be overridden (and default that in the docker image), then it should work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17753294" author="houston" created="Fri, 11 Aug 2023 17:46:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16150&quot; title=&quot;Provide correct bound zookeeper interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-16150&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-16150&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is affected because we don&apos;t want to use the bind address as the address blindly. We want to use the loopback address if the bind address is set to bind-all (0.0.0.0).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m pretty sure its safest to choose the IP address instead of the hostname, which was the original idea for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16150&quot; title=&quot;Provide correct bound zookeeper interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-16150&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-16150&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, so I&apos;ll go with that as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17753339" author="houston" created="Fri, 11 Aug 2023 20:05:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually we don&apos;t want to use the loopback address, we will use the same logic that is used to determine the default SOLR_HOST (advertised SolrNode name) if none is given. This defaults to the (best) IP of the host.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17754140" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 14 Aug 2023 15:17:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 3b2b1b7f790986c84671c505e8055afb4dc59c76 in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/main from Houston Putman&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=3b2b1b7f790&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=3b2b1b7f790&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16926&quot; title=&quot;Embedded ZK not reachable via docker&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-16926&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-16926&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Give override for EmbeddedZK bind host (#1836)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17754151" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 14 Aug 2023 15:30:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 6deab732415cf5ac5a4423f922849bd2b8f25e9c in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/branch_9x from Houston Putman&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=6deab732415&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=6deab732415&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16926&quot; title=&quot;Embedded ZK not reachable via docker&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-16926&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-16926&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Give override for EmbeddedZK bind host (#1836)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(cherry picked from commit 3b2b1b7f790986c84671c505e8055afb4dc59c76)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17764569" author="dsmiley" created="Wed, 13 Sep 2023 09:33:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d argue the concept of a bind host restriction, when it comes processes in a container, is an obsolete concept. &#160;It&apos;s up to the person running the Docker container to explicitly expose the ports desired.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17775479" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Sun, 15 Oct 2023 19:57:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing after the 9.4.0 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
